description:
"Treasure Hunt with Death": The greedy relatives of a recently-deceased man hold a seance to force him to reveal his hidden treasure.

"The House on Brook Street": A widow discovers her late husband's secret life as a black-magic cult leader.

"The Triple Cross": An old man fakes his death to learn his heir's true character.

"Let's Face It": A double-crossing businessman learns that his new accomplice is actually his old partner, having had plastic surgery.

"The Couple Next Door": Overbearing Mrs. Slader bullies her henpecked husband into "keeping up with the Joneses." Whatever Mr. Jones gives his wife, Mrs. Slader demands the same from her husband. One day, Mr. Jones gives his wife a bullet in the head...

"The Pit of Fear": Fed up with his imps' laziness, Satan hires an efficiency expert to restore Hades to its proper working order.

"The Watchers": A scientist theorizes the existence of an alien race observing and guiding humanity's advancement.

"Fight for Life": Two seafaring brothers reveal their true characters as the ship sinks.

"The Next World": A suicide finds himself in a topsy-turvy afterlife.

"I Love a Mermaid": A sailor falls in love with a mermaid.

Formerly Dotty.

Can either of them survive?

The Exiles have been split apart by a spell from a mortally wounded union Jack. Nocturne and Sunfire find themselves on a familiar world.

The world in which the legacy virus and Phalanx had merged into an unstoppable virus that converted the world. Now though things are looking better and Sunfire seems to have found someone who could be more then a friend...

description: Reunited after falling prey to a disastrous chaos spell that split them into smaller factions on different worlds, the Exiles visit a little piece of super hero history as they stowaway on the first mission of the Fantastic Four.
name: Fantastic Voyage (part 1 of 3)

description:
The Exiles are left to teach the newly formed Fantastic Four the ropes of super-heroism, as there are no other heros in the world. As the Exiles help the Fantastic Four learn their new powers the group splits up. Mimic and Sasquatch take on the Thing, with much battering around and a fall off the Brooklyn Bridge, Mimic and Sasquatch manage to slow down the Thing. As Mimic pulls Sasquatch out of the water, Thing clocks him in his flesh form; Calvin is hurt internally and cannot revert to metal form.

He instructs Heather to kill him revealing that he was not on the Brood Planet for six months but for four years and he has been implanted with a Brood Egg. Heather tells him no one is going to kill him and Calvin turns into a child of the Brood. Morph and Mr. Fantastic go to a lab where Tony Stark and Dr. Octavius help them to find a way to reboot Thing and help calm him down. They build a ray machine and shoot Thing with it just as he is about to attack Sasquatch. Sunfire, Nocturne, Magik, Human Torch, and Invisible Woman help out in the city, getting people out of the way of danger.
name: Fantastic Voyage (part 2 of 3)

description:
Mimic has sustained severe injuries while battling the Thing and is overtaken by a Brood Egg that had been festering inside his body.

The Exiles now face their leader as he becomes a creature bent on Earth's destruction.
name: Fantastic Voyage (part 3 of 3)
